## 1. Reflection: Coding in Markdown
**Situation:** As part of the PRP370S assessment, I was required to design a digital portfolio and code my CV using Markdown language[cite: 109, 110, 115]. 

**Task:** My objective was to use GitHub Flavored Markdown (GFM) to create a structured, web-ready document that includes professional formatting without using a complex word processor.

**Action:** I researched GFM syntax for headers, lists, and links. I specifically focused on creating a clean hierarchy for my CV and ensuring that all technical skills were easily scannable using bullet points.

**Result:** I successfully created a responsive CV that renders perfectly on GitHub. This process improved my ability to use lightweight markup languages, which is essential for developer documentation.

